23/09/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- Pope Benedict XVI accepted an invitation on Friday (September 21st) to visit Albania in the near future. The invitation was extended by Prime Minister Sali Berisha, who had an audience at the pope's summer residence at Castel Gandolfo. Berisha, leader of the Albanian Democratic Party, was in Italy attending a conference of conservative and right-wing parties. (BIRN, Makfax, B92 - 22/09/07)
